cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks related to face parsing, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel RoI Tanh-warping operator, which involves the use of neural networks, making it relevant to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of hierarchical local-based methods and global methods, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper proposes a new approach for face parsing that surpasses state-of-the-art methods, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
